for(x in 0:2){
  for (y in 0:2){
    for (m in 1:2){
      for (n in 0:2){
        cat("ARMA(", x, ", ", y, ") with GARCH(", m, ", ", n, ")")
          result = garchFit(formula = substitute(~arma(p,q)+garch(i,j),
                                              list(p=x,
                                                   q=y,
                                                   i=m,
                                                   j=n)), 
                         data = coredata(return), 
                         cond.dist = "norm")
          cat("AIC: ", result@fit$ics[1]*nrow(return))
          print("")
          print("-------------------------------------------------")
      }
    }
  }
}
